The course is focused on consumer choice, producer theory, partial and general equilibrium . The objective of the course to deepen the understanding of the technical details of modern microeconomics with emphasis on mathematical tools. Students will be assumed to be familiar with algebra, calculus including constrained optimization, and basic probability.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Teach students to applying microeconomic methods in real-world problems. The course will give introduction to the most popular modelling methodsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject: * knows the more popular ways in economics to describe preferences, production, and decision-making; * knows a selection of simpler widely used techniques for microeconomic modelling; * is familiar with a selection of standard models in the literature; * can apply models, and model-based thinking in everyday situations.
